{"blocks":[{"key":"4ptc","text":"qPCR for the quantification of Aquarickettsia spp. ( Klinges et al., 2022) a putative parasite found in the coral A. cervicornis. This protocol has been altered by incorporating a recently published A. cervicornis control gene (Palacio-Castro et al., 2021)  targeted to detect differences across A. cervicornis genotypes because it is a single-copy gene in A. cervicornis.
